			<div class="content" id="post-content-3772592">
									

<blockquote>
<p>However, wouldn't the 05 council/the Foundation at large be concerned that any GOI can now use these non-anomalous amnestics?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I operate on the assumption that other major GOI's already have their own equivalent of amnestics, and wouldn't be too interested in unreliable street amnestics.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Additionally, I'd like some clarification on exactly which amnestics are non-anomalous, and I'm not sure how mnestics work now.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yes, the mnestics described in this piece are also non-anomalous. They work the same way as the amnestics do: memory affecting drugs (which are real) packed inside nanoparticles that are designed to target only specific types of neural pathways or brain areas.</p>
<p>Within this piece, anomalous amnestics (from the Eel, the Laughing Men and the Phone Sex Cacti) still exist, but are gradually being phased out because non-anomalous amnestics are easier to obtain.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>+1 from me. I get excited when I see your name next to a piece, keep up the solid work.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Thank you!</p>

