														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3763544">
									

<p>I remember seeing this in the forums. Looks much nicer polished up now! +1 from me, for the setup you've got here.</p>
<p>I particularly like these:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Class E, Ennui: To induce psychological complacency with the anomalous</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Class F, Fugue: For erasing and rebuilding the subject's identity</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Class G, Gaslighting: To cause subjects to doubt the authenticity of their memories</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I mean, IRL scientists have already figured out plenty of information about how the brain works and how different parts affect memory and cognition and whatnot, so imagine what Foundation scientists know. And they would definitely make these sorts of things. Chilling to think about.</p>

							</div>

								
					
